msItem.title: A festival prayer book for Rosh ha-Shanah and Yom Kipur.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1 ; ruled lines: 15; written lines: 14; Uniform layout. Initial words in large square characters. Catchwords on every page. Visible hard-point ruling. Marbled binding ends and gauffered edges.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Byzantine square and semi-cursive script of the 17th century.

binding.p: BM in-house. Spine: 'Services for New Year & Day of Atonement. Corfu Rite. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Oriental 6425.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: M.N. Adler Esq.: purchased from him by the British Museum on 14 July 1902: inscribed, folio [190v].
